EFF members of parliament ahead of the State of the Nation Address. JOHANNESBURG - Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) leader Julius Malema and his wife Mantwa will consider dropping a R2-million lawsuit against ANC MP Boy Mamabolo. Mamabolo issued an apology on Thursday after his outburst in Parliament, accusing Malema of abusing Mantwa. READ: Malema's wife files defamation suit against ANC's Mamabolo The ANC MP says he was 'influenced' by the so-called 'Mantwa's-friends'. He wasn't the only one who has said sorry. READ: Malema responds to Ramaphosa apology Malema has also apologised to President Cyril Ramaphosa and his family. That's after stating that the President was abusive to his late, ex-wife.